adviseScripts.text: Ugh... It's so hot!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Aaah! I'm practically melting!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Coach, how can I keep myself from getting too hot?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Put an ice cube in your mouth.
Would hugging me help?
Mmm, that does sound like a good idea...
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: But, no thanks.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: If I did that, I wouldn't be able to talk with you, Coach!.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Really? Are you sure?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Your body is always so cool, Coach. It feels so good!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Thank you so much!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I research ways to make the heat bearable with Folkwang.
I was talking to Rumani...
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: that I started taking ice supplements to change my constitution but she got really mad.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Do you have any idea why?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Because you chose supplements instead of exercise.
She just doesn't like ice supplements.
No way! Do you really think that's the reason?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I know Rumani likes exercising but not to that extent...
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Nah. I don't think that's it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Oh? I think you're right.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I gave her some after working out...
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: and she said she wouldn't eat them! Plus she must have been really hot!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Now that my head's a little cooler, I've figured it out!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I talk more with Folkwang about Rumani.
Hey, Coach.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Why do people sweat?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I don't think it makes our lives better at all.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Sweating helps adjust your body temperature.
Your body sweats just to give you a hard time.
Help adjust your body temperature?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Then why doesn't it ever work?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: My body is always so hot!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: It doesn't make any sense!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Right? I knew it was just to give me a hard time!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Ugh! Sweat... I'll never forgive you...
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I have a sweaty conversation with Folkwang.
I have a question for you, Coach.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: if there are one that can't stand the cold and one who can't stand the heat,
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: would you turn the air conditioner on or off?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I think turning it on would be right.
I think turning it off would be for the best.
Right! You've gotta turn it on!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: If they get cold, they should just wear a jacket.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: But someone who feels hot can't just take all their clothes off!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Uh... Epinel, we will see about this!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Is that really the right choice?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Then, I might just die...
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I'll melt into a little puddle...
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I turn the air conditioning up for Folkwang, who was feeling a bit hot.
Coach, what kind of weather do you like the most?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Sunny days.
Cloudy days.
I don't like sunny days.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: They're always too hot for me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Me, too! Cloudy days are the best.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I used to love rainy days more...
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: The rain always felt like it was washing away my sweat.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: But, there aren't many rainy days in the Ark, and getting wet in the rain makes me feel uncomfortable.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: That's why I prefer cloudy days now.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Folkwang about the weather.
Coach, you haven't used your vacation days yet, but when you do...
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: where will you go?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: The Commander's Room.
The swimming pool.
Of course, the Commander's Room is cool. And it's nice if Coach is there...
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: But wouldn't it be a little boring to go there for vacation?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Really? You really want to go to the swimming pool?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Then, take me with you!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I love taking a dip!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Folkwang about vacations.
Do you think everyone in the world
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: hates sweaty people?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: If they do, it'd really hurt my feelings.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: ... Good luck with that.
No, of course not. They don't hate sweaty people...
Coach, you make me feel even worse.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: *Sniff* Thanks, Coach.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Coach always takes better care of me than anyone else!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I listen to Folkwang about the sufferings of sweaty people.
Recently, I get the feeling that Epinel thinks that I'm a little pathetic.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Whenever our eyes meet, she always keeps shaking her head!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: But, I'm even older than she is!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Are you sure you're older?
Then try to be more understanding of her, since you are older.
Uh... Maybe I'm not.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: After all, Nikkes never look like their true age...
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: From now, I'll be careful with how I treat Epinel.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: That's exactly the kind of answer I expected from you, Coach.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Even though I might not be older,
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I will still try to understand her because I physically look older!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Folkwang about Epinel.
Sugar keeps saying that biking is the best way to keep your cool while moving.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: But, no matter how I think about it, I think running is better.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: What do you think, Coach?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Running is the best.
Cycling is better.
Exactly!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: When you run forward, the cool wind hits your face!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: The air feels really good on my legs, too!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: You know me best of all!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: You really think so, Coach?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I can't believe it. I thought you'd understand me..
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I feel a little sad now...
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Folkwang about how amazing running is.
Coach, what type of ice Splendamin do you like most?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Soda ice Splendamin is my favorite!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I don't really like ice Splendamin...
Want me to get you some?
What? Why not?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: It's so delicious. What's not to like?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: You know nothing about cold food, Coach!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: You mean, now?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I always feel so touched by your kindness, Coach!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I have a good time with Folkwang.
When you've been running for a long time, sometimes you'll suddenly get a second wind.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: There's a word to describe this, what was it called again?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Runner's high.
Driver's high.
Ah, that's right!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Have you ever experienced that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: If you haven't, do you want to go running?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Hmm... Isn't that a name of a song?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I think it was the opening theme to a teen drama... was it GTX?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Folkwang instilled the joy of running in me.
All right, I've made up my mind.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I'm going to quit being an athlete and become a doctor.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Have you grown bored with playing sports?
Is that just because you'll have plenty of nurses around to wipe off your sweat?
What? Absolutely not!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: It's just... I sweat so darn much, that I was wondering what I could do about it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I was just thinking out loud, don't pay me any mind.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: H-how did you know?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I can't believe you guessed that!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Folkwang and I started to look into what you had to study to become a doctor.
... and abandoned the plan 30 minutes later.
When you run in the morning, you get to meet a lot of people.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I ran into this little girl who is simply adorable. I could just pinch her cheeks.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Do you think it'd be all right if I said hi to her?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Sure, go for it.
You might freak her out.
You're right. I just need to put my apprehension aside and go for it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I'll go up to her tomorrow!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Well, in that case...
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I guess I'll wait a bit more before approaching her.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Folkwang and I went over ways to greet people in a friendly manner.
I was looking at the recommended dosage for this supplement I have,
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: when a thought suddenly occurred to me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: If you took more than the recommended amount, wouldn't they be even more effective?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: They don't call it the recommended dosage for anything.
I think you may be onto something.
But two is better than one, and three is better than two.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: What's wrong with that logic?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I'll test it out later.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I think so too!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I'm gonna go down my entire stash of supplements!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Straight down the hatch!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: That evening, Folkwang suffered from stomach pains.
I finally found a way to deal with my sweating problem!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: All I've got to do...
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: is slap maxi pads all over my body!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Won't that weigh you down?
That is a genius idea!
Hmm, that's a good point.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Sure, I won't be wet with sweat, but I'll be so weighed down that I won't be able to run properly.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Are there any pads that get your sweat to evaporate?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Exactly! It's foolproof!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I'll go try it right now...
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: On second thought, that won't work. It'd only end up weighing me down.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Folkwang and I try to come up with other methods to alleviate her perspiration issue.
Whenever I see myself sweating, I can't help but feel
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: it might make the people around me feel uncomfortable...
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: You shouldn't worry about what other people think.
It's okay, because your sweat actually smells quite nice.
I shouldn't?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Since I'm an athlete, I always thought it was normal to care about what other people think.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: But, if you say I shouldn't, then I won't!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Wh-what did you say?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: When did you have a chance to smell me before?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Wait, are you doing it right now?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: S-stop! Plug up your nose!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Folkwang and I share our opinions on the matter.
Being in battle can be a terrifying thing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Even though combat is second nature to a Nikke, I can't help but feel a little scared.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Do you know any methods to deal with this?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Let's try finding a supplement that makes you enjoy combat.
Have faith in your squadmates.
I can't believe I didn't think of that!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I'm not sure if that's something supplements can help with, but
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I'll see what I can find.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: But... I'm the only one who gets scared.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: What does trusting my squadmates have to do with this?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Folkwang and I look into different methods to help her overcome her fear.
Epinel once asked me
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: why I prefer running when it's so much faster to ride a board.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: It got me thinking... why exactly do I prefer it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: With running, you can gain momentum without any outside assistance.
Because you feel alive when you run.
You're right.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: When I run, I have to depend on nothing but my own strength to make me gain speed.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Kicking off from the ground and running with my back to the wind... I can't get enough of it!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: So... if I stop running, I'd die?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: That can't be right...
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Folkwang and I talk about how much running means to her.
Come to think of it, I've never seen you take any supplements.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: You should take some with me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I'll recommend you a good one.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I'm already quite healthy, so it's okay.
I'm already taking some.
You don't take supplements for immediate health benefits.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: It's a long-term investment.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: So you should really start taking them now.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Really? What do you take?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Can you show me what you're taking?
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I can have a look at its nutritional components.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Folkwang and I have a back and forth about supplements.
Ugh... I trained with Rumani and my entire body feels so sore now.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: She really put me through the wringer.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Call it what you will, but I call it abuse.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: She's just doing her best to help you.
You're right, let's go talk to her.
Hmm... well, when you put it like that...
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: She's probably just doing what she feels is best for me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: ... But that doesn't change the fact that I'm in pain.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Yes! Let's give her a piece of our minds!
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Actually, now that I think about it, I've never adjusted my pace when I go jogging with her.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: I think we're both just trying to lift each other up.
adviseScripts.speaker: Folkwang

adviseScripts.text: Folkwang and I talk more about members of Nepenthe.
